 and australia over the course of two decades carlyle has amassed a portfolio of  billion in assets under management across  funds and  fund of fund vehicles and has made investments in more than  companies and more than  real estate investments in  carlyle completed a  million initial public offering and began trading on the nasdaq stock exchange on may   according to a  ranking called the pei  based on capital raised over the last five years carlyle was ranked no  as the largest private equity firm in the world contents  business segments  corporate private equity  real assets  global market strategies  investment solutions  history  founding and early history  –  since   ownership changes  subsidiaries and jointventures  carlyle capital corporation  in documentaries  notable employees and advisors  business  politicians  media  see also  references  notes and references  external links business segmentsedit the firm is organized into four business segments corporate private equity – management of carlyles family of private equity funds investing primarily in leveraged buyout and growth capital transactions through a range of geographically focused investment funds real assets – management of carlyles family of energy and real estate investment funds focusing on the us europe and asia global market strategies – management of various credit equities and hedge fund vehicles with over  billion in assets under management and investment solutions – management of three investment groups corporate private equity real estate and liquid market solutions which invest in primary secondary and coinvestments commingled funds and separately managed accounts corporate private equityedit carlyles corporate private equity division manages a series of leveraged buyout and growth capital investment funds with specific geographic or industry focuses carlyle invests primarily in the following industries aerospace defense  government services consumer  retail energy financial services health care industrial real estate technology and business services telecommunications  media and transportation as of december   carlyle managed  active funds with  billion in assets under management consisting of buyout funds – carlyle manages a group of  active funds with approximately  billion in assets under management as of december   growth capital funds – carlyle manages  active growth capital funds with approximately  billion in assets under management as of december   real assetsedit carlyles real assets division manages  active investment funds focused on real estate infrastructure and energy and natural resources the real assets business has two primary areas of focus real estate funds – carlyle manages  active real estate funds with approximately  billion in assets under management as of december   energy natural resources  carlyle manages eight funds advised by carlyle energy affiliate ngp energy capital management with approximately  billion in assets under management as of december   two power funds with approximately  billion in assets under management as of december   and one international energy fund with approximately  billion in assets under management as of december   global market strategiesedit carlyles global market strategies division manages  investment across a range of investments including credit emerging markets macroeconomic strategies commodities trading leveraged loans structured credit and mezzanine debt as of december   the global market strategies division had  billion of assets under management across several strategies structured credit funds – carlyle manages  investment funds including clos with approximately  billion in assets under management as of december   distressed and corporate opportunities – carlyle manages  funds focused on investments in distressed debt with approximately  billion in assets under management as of december   mezzanine – carlyle manages  funds focused on mezzanine debt investments in middle market c