als and over  employees carlyles real estate fund of funds group is called metropolitan which provides investors with access to multimanager real estate funds and solutions with more than  fund managers in the united states europe asia and latin america metropolitan constructs and manages us nonus and global real estate portfolios which include primary and secondary fund interests as well as coinvestments dgam is carlyles liquid solutions team dgam provides investors access to an array of proprietary and thirdparty hedge funds around the world dgam works to manage the complexities of alternative asset classes with a complementary blend of investment and operations expertise historyedit history of private equity and venture capital early history origins of modern private equity the s leveraged buyout boom the s leveraged buyout and the venture capital bubble the s dotcom bubble to the credit crunch v t e founding and early historyedit carlyle was founded in  as an investment banking boutique by five original partners with backgrounds in finance and government william e conway jr stephen l norris david m rubenstein daniel a daniello and greg rosenbaum the founding partners named the firm after the carlyle hotel in new york city where norris and rubenstein had often met to discuss the formation of their new investment business rubenstein who was a washingtonbased lawyer had worked in the carter administration norris and daneillo had previously worked together at marriott corporation while conway was a finance executive at mci communications of the founding five partners rubenstein conway and daneillo remain active in the business while rosenbaum left in the first year and norris departed in  carlyle was founded with  million of financial backing from t rowe price alex brown  sons first interstate equities and the richard king mellon family in the late s carlyle raised capital on a dealbydeal basis to pursue leveraged buyout investments including a failed takeover battle for chichis the firm raised its first dedicated buyout fund with  million of investor commitments in  in its early years carlyle also advised in transactions including a  million investment by prince alwaleed bin talal a member of the saudi royal family in citigroup in  the crusader weapon system developed by united defense carlyles largest investment in the defense industry was cancelled in may  carlyle initially developed a reputation for acquiring businesses related to the defense industry in  carlyle completed the acquisition of the electronics division of general dynamics corporation renamed gde systems a producer of military electronics systems carlyle would later sell the business to tracor in october  carlyle acquired magnavox electronic systems the military communications and electronicwarfare systems segment of magnavox from philips electronics in  carlyle sold magnavox for approximately  million to hughes aircraft company in  carlyle also invested in vought aircraft through a partnership with northrop grumman carlyles most notable defense industry investment came in october  with its acquisition of united defense industries the  million acquisition of united defense represented carlyles largest investment to that point carlyle was able to complete an ipo of united defense on the new york stock exchange in december  selling a significant portion of its interest in the company carlyle completed a sale of its remaining united defense stock and exited the investment in april  in more recent years carlyle has deemphasized its focus on defense industry investments carlyles  investor conference took place on september   in the weeks following the meeting it was reported that shafiq bin laden a member of the bin laden family had been the guest of honor and that they were investors in carlyle managed funds later reports confirmed that the bin laden family had invested  million into carlyles  billion carlyle partners ii fund in  making the family relatively small investors with the firm however their overall investment might have been considerably larger with the  million committed in  only being an initial contribution that grew over time these connections would later be profiled in michael moores fahrenheit  the bin laden family liquidated its holdings in carlyles funds in october  just after the september th attacks when the connection of their family name to the carlyle groups name became impolitic –edit the carlyle group logo following the collapse of the dotcom bubble in  and  buyout activity declined significantly marked by the twostage buyout of dex media at the end of  and  large multibilliondollar us buyouts could once again obtain significant high yield debt financing and larger transactions could be completed carlyle together with welsh carson anderson  stowe led a  billion buyout of qwestdex the buyout was the third largest corporate buyout since  qwestdexs purchase occurred in two stages a  billion acquisition of assets known as dex media east in november  and a  billion acquisition of assets known as dex media west in  r h donnelley corporation acquired dex media in  shortly after dex media other larger buyouts would be completed signaling the resurgence in private equity was underway lou gerstner former chairman and ceo of ibm and nabisco was appointed chairman of carlyle in january  replacing frank carlucci gerstner would serve in that position through october  the hiring of gerstner was intended to reduce the perception of carlyle as a politically dominated firm at the time carlyle which had been founded  years earlier had accumulated  billion of assets under management and had generated annualized returns for investors of  carlyle also announced the  billion acquisition of hawaiian telcom from verizon in may  carlyles investment was immediately challenged when hawaii regulators delayed the closing of the buyout the company also suffered billing and customerservice issues as it had to recreate its backoffice systems hawaiian telcom ultimately filed for bankruptcy in december  costing carlyle the  million it had invested in the company carlyle led the  billion buyout of hertz in  as the activity of the large private equity firms increased in the mids carlyle kept pace with such competitors as kohlberg kravis roberts blackstone group and tpg capital in  carlyle together with clayton dubilier  rice and merrill lynch completed the  billion leveraged buyout of the hertz corporation the largest car rental agency from ford the following year in august  carlyle and its riverstone holdings affiliate partnered with goldman sachs capital partners in the  billion including assumed debt acquisition of kinder morgan one of the largest pipeline operators in the us the buyout was backed by richard kinder the companys cofounder and a former president of enron in september  carlyle led a consortium comprising blackstone group permira and tpg capital in the  billion takeover of freescale semiconductor at the time of its announcement freescale would be the largest leveraged buyout of a technology company ever surpassing the  buyout of sungard the buyers were forced to pay an extra  million because kkr made a lastminute bid as the original deal was about to be signed shortly after the deal closed in late  cell phone sales at motorola corp freescales former corporate parent and a major customer began dropping sharply in addition in the recession of – freescales chip sales to automakers fell off and the company came under great financial strain earlier that year in january  carlyle together with blackstone group alpinvest partners hellman  friedman kohlberg kravis roberts and thomas h lee partners acquired nielsen company the global information and media company formerly known as vnu in an  billion buyout also in  carlyle acquired oriental trading company which ultimately declared bankruptcy in august  as well as forba dental management the owner of small smiles dental centers the largest us chain of dental clinics for children since edit david rubenstein the head of the carlyle group the largest private equity firm by investor commitments during the – buyout boom on january   the carlyle group purchased synagro technologies a municipal sludge hauler and spreader for  per share carlyle continued to make large investments into  as the buyout market reached its peak in june  carlyle agrees to acquire hd supply for  billion along with bain capital and clayton dubilier  rice with each agreeing to buy a onethird stake in the division home depot sold their wholesale construction supply business to fund a stock repurchase estimated at  billion also in june  carlyle announced that it would partner with onex corporation to buy the allison transmission unit from general motors for  billion on december   david rubenstein representing the carlyle group purchased the magna carta one of seventeen copies at sothebys auction house in new york city he paid the perot foundation  million mr rubenstein expressed his intent for it to be returned to the national archives for display on may   booz allen hamilton announced that it would sell a majority stake in the us government business to the carlyle group for  billion the transaction was expected to be complete july   in november  the carlyle group was named private equity firm of the year in the us at the financial timesmergermarket  ma awards in march  new york state and federal authorities began an investigation into payments made by carlyles riverstone holdings subsidiary to placement agents allegedly made in exchange for investments from the new york state common retirement system the states pension fund in  carlyle had entered into a joint venture with riverstone holdings an energy and power focused private equity firm founded by pierre f lapeyre jr and david m leuschen it was alleged that these payments were in fact bribes or kickbacks made to pension officials who have been under investigation by new york state a